    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2025-01-15</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2025-07-07T16:34:25Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pony Up Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill requires the U.S. Postal Service (USPS) to pay a citizen for late payment fees or penalties incurred due to late delivery of mail by USPS.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Late delivery of mail means that (1) USPS received a bill or notice of bill at least 12 days prior to the payment due date and delivered such bill or notice of bill less than 6 days prior to the payment due date; or (2) USPS received a payment at least 5 days prior to the payment due date and delivered such payment after the due date.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;USPS is not required to pay a citizen for late payment fees or penalties when a bill, notice of bill, or payment is delayed for reasons outside of USPS control (for example, if a major disaster or emergency declared by the President caused the delay).&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
